Package com.scalien.scaliendb

Class Summary
ByteRangeParams ByteRangeParams is a convenient way to specify the byte[] parameters for iteration when using Table.getKeyIterator(ByteRangeParams), Table.getKeyValueIterator(ByteRangeParams) and Table.count(ByteRangeParams).
Client The ScalienDB client represents a connection to a ScalienDB cluster.
Database Database is a convenience class for encapsulating database related operations.
Quorum Quorum is a convenience class for working wit quorums.
Sequence Sequence is a class for atomically retrieving unique integer IDs using a key whose value stores the next ID as a piece of text.
Status Collection of ScalienDB client status codes.
StringRangeParams StringRangeParams is a convenient way to specify the string parameters for iteration when using Table.getKeyIterator(StringRangeParams), Table.getKeyValueIterator(StringRangeParams) and Table.count(StringRangeParams).
Table Table is a convenience class for encapsulating table related operations.
